<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880216-0064 </DOCNO><HL> Regulators Close 3 Banks Across U.S., FDIC Reports </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GOVMT ZION </CO><IN> BNK TNM </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Regulators closed banks in Michigan, Florida and Utah, bringing bank failures nationwide this year to 23, the Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. said.    The sole office of First State Bank, White Cloud, Mich., reopened yesterday as a branch of Peoples State Bank, St. Joseph, Mich. First State had assets of $38.7 million when it was closed by state regulators Friday. Peoples State assumes its $36.5 million in deposits and is purchasing certain loans and other assets for $26 million.    Also closed Friday was Global Bank, Hialeah, Fla., which had assets of $18.7 million. Its office is to reopen today as a branch of Ocean Bank, Miami. Ocean Bank assumes $19.2 million in deposits and is purchasing loans and other assets for $13.1 million.    And in Vernal, Utah, Basin State Bank's sole office is to reopen today as a branch of Zions First National Bank, Salt Lake City, which assumes its $11.3 million in deposits. Basin State's assets totaled $11.8 million when state regulators closed it Friday. </TEXT></DOC>